# Pre-Commit Checklist

## Tools
- [ ] Code formatted by Pint
- [ ] PHPStan without errors
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] GitLeaks doesn't detect secrets
- [ ] Composer audit doesn't detect critical vulnerabilities

## Tests (TDD - MANDATORY)
- [ ] **BEFORE code:** Test written (RED) - test FAILS ✅
- [ ] **AFTER code:** Code written (GREEN) - test PASSES ✅
- [ ] **AFTER refactoring:** Refactored (REFACTOR) - tests still PASS ✅
- [ ] New code has tests (if it's a new feature)
- [ ] Tests are readable
- [ ] **TDD was followed in correct order** (RED → GREEN → REFACTOR)

## Quality
- [ ] Code readable and follows conventions
- [ ] SOLID applied (when it makes sense)
- [ ] Duplication removed (when needed)
- [ ] Type hints and `declare(strict_types=1)`

## Cleanup
- [ ] No debug code
- [ ] No unused code
- [ ] No commented code (unless it explains "why")

## Git
- [ ] Commit message is descriptive and follows convention
- [ ] Commit message is in English (REQUIRED)
- [ ] PR title is in English (REQUIRED)
- [ ] PR description is in English (REQUIRED)
- [ ] Commit contains one logical change
